radiographic_examinations.findings: Appendix dilated measuring up to 1.1 cm with mild adjacent fat stranding, consistent with acute appendicitis. No evidence of perforation or pneumoperitoneum. Visualized lung fields, liver, pancreas, spleen, adrenal glands, kidneys, gastrointestinal tract, and pelvic organs are within normal limits. No evidence of lymphadenopathy or osseous lesions.
